Reference domain.

We continue with the same fintech consumer bank. Two tables drive this notebook.

The first is silver dot customers — the shared dimension you stood up at the end of the first notebook. The second is a new one, silver dot card transactions. This is the busiest fact table in the bank, the one the fraud and machine learning teams care about most.

Keep those two in mind. Almost every example here — acid, time travel, merge, maintenance — is shown against card transactions, because it's the table that's written constantly and read constantly.
